    <article class="markdown-body entry-content" itemprop="text"><h1><a id="user-content-gravizo" class="anchor" href="#gravizo" aria-hidden="true"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>gravizo</h1>

<p>How to include graphviz graphs in github README.md</p>

<p>Only need to include image markdown tag with the url <a href="http://www.gravizo.com">http://g.gravizo.com/g?</a> followed by your description graph in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DOT_(graph_description_language)">DOT syntax</a>, <a href="http://www.umlgraph.org/doc/cd-intro.html">UMLGraph</a>, <a href="http://plantuml.sourceforge.net/sequence.html">PlantUML</a> or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scalable_Vector_Graphics">SVG</a> :</p>

<p><a href="https://camo.githubusercontent." target="_blank"><img src="https://camo.githubusercontent." alt="Alt text" data-canonical-src="http://g.gravizo.com/g?%0A%20%20digraph%20G%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20aize%20=%224,4%22;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20%5Bshape=box%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20parse%20%5Bweight=8%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20parse%20-%3E%20execute;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20init%20%5Bstyle=dotted%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20cleanup;%0A%20%20%20%20execute%20-%3E%20%7B%20make_string;%20printf%7D;%0A%20%20%20%20init%20-%3E%20make_string;%0A%20%20%20%20edge%20%5Bcolor=red%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20printf%20%5Bstyle=bold,label=%22100%20times%22%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20make_string%20%5Blabel=%22make%20a%20string%22%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20node%20%5Bshape=box,style=filled,color=%22.7%20.3%201.0%22%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20execute%20-%3E%20compare;%0A%20%20%7D" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>

<div class="highlight highlight-text-html-basic"><pre>![Alt text](http://g.gravizo.com/g?
  digraph G {
    aize ="4,4";
    main [shape=box];
    main -&gt; parse [weight=8];
    parse -&gt; execute;
    main -&gt; init [style=dotted];
    main -&gt; cleanup;
    execute -&gt; { make_string; printf};
    init -&gt; make_string;
    edge [color=red];
    main -&gt; printf [style=bold,label="100 times"];
    make_string [label="make a string"];
    node [shape=box,style=filled,color=".7 .3 1.0"];
    execute -&gt; compare;
  }
)</pre></div>

<p>This allow to include your graphs in the README, and still redeable in normal text editor.</p>

<p><strong>SVG output</strong> it's ready. Only need to replace <a href="http://g.gravizo.com/g">http://g.gravizo.com/g</a>? by <a href="http://g.gravizo.com/svg">http://g.gravizo.com/svg</a>? and <a href="http://g.gravizo.com/source">http://g.gravizo.com/source</a>? by <a href="http://g.gravizo.com/source/svg">http://g.gravizo.com/source/svg</a>?</p>

<p><a href="https://camo.githubusercontent." target="_blank"><img src="https://camo.githubusercontent." alt="Alt text" data-canonical-src="http://g.gravizo.com/svg?%0A%20%20digraph%20G%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20aize%20=%224,4%22;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20%5Bshape=box%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20parse%20%5Bweight=8%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20parse%20-%3E%20execute;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20init%20%5Bstyle=dotted%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20cleanup;%0A%20%20%20%20execute%20-%3E%20%7B%20make_string;%20printf%7D;%0A%20%20%20%20init%20-%3E%20make_string;%0A%20%20%20%20edge%20%5Bcolor=red%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20main%20-%3E%20printf%20%5Bstyle=bold,label=%22100%20times%22%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20make_string%20%5Blabel=%22make%20a%20string%22%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20node%20%5Bshape=box,style=filled,color=%22.7%20.3%201.0%22%5D;%0A%20%20%20%20execute%20-%3E%20compare;%0A%20%20%7D" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>

<h3><a id="user-content-new-the-indirect-way" class="anchor" href="#new-the-indirect-way" aria-hidden="true"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>New. The indirect way.</h3>

<p>You can use indirect way to refer a source file as graph description.
